sql:
SELECT AVG(balance) AS average_balance, account_number
FROM accounts
GROUP BY account_number;

external_knowledge:
- "hidden treasures" refers to the aggregated financial data;
- "financial landscape" represents the wealth distribution within departments;
- "average wealth of the collective employee accounts" translates to the average balance of all employee accounts within a department;
- "names and departments of every employee" refers to the employee's name and department in the query;
- "maritime explorers" is a metaphor for the employees being the subjects of the financial journey represented by their accounts;
- "unique identifiers" refers to employee IDs.

sql:
SELECT a.account_id, e.name
FROM accounts a
INNER JOIN employees e ON a.tin = e.tin;

SELECT e.name
FROM employees e
INNER JOIN accounts a ON e.employee_id = a.employee_id
WHERE a.balance > (
    SELECT AVG(balance) FROM accounts
);

external_knowledge:
- "sailing captains" refers to employees eligible for work-from-home benefits; 
- "navigate their ships from the comfort of their homes" refers to employees who are eligible for work-from-home (WFH) benefits; 
- "treasure chest" metaphorically refers to an account; 
- "more than half a million gold coins" refers to a balance greater than $500,000; 
- "fleet" represents the collective accounts of an employee; 
- "average wealth of their fleet" refers to the average balance across the accounts linked to an employee.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(account_id) AS active_accounts_count
FROM accounts
WHERE account_status = 'Active' AND closing_date IS NULL;
